the whole gosh-darn zone? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=desra>desra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/29/03 12:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4976.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.myimgs.com/data/kd7apq/lgdeswhitetrans.gif height=199 width=112></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tips for fighting in the Warrens</span><hr size=1> don't let them get away. if you can cast snare or root. if you're a mage use your earth elemental. They seem to run early and fast, then return with friends <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.myimgs.com/data/kd7apq/desraname.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:comic sans ms;font-size:x-small;">Enchanting for 29 seasons</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
