Bubbles is teh win<br>
j00 r teh sux<br>
stick it where?</span><br>  Posts: 594<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/29/03 2:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4976.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.boomspeed.com/warden4423/link.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tips for fighting in the Warrens</span><hr size=1> The Warrens are friggin EVIL. EVIL I say!! I hate that place. <br>
<br>
Even when the kobolds are green, they will run and bring back dozens of other kobolds and swarm ya. I've almost died there a few times just faction grinding on those damn green kobolds. <br>
<br>
As Desra said, root em or snare em if ya can. Your a paladin now, I think, and I'd say stun em if you got it already. If your exping there and plan on staying, head up to the bazaar and buy a few crystaline nets. 5ppish a pop, 3 casts of root. Not a bad little item. Course, that will get expensive quick.  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.boomspeed.com/warden4423/newzaith2.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Knight of Quellious<br>
Cleric of Bristlebane</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqpixelarmy.com/" target="top">Cannon Fodder for the EQPA!</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wyrdup>Wyrd Up</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1061<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/29/03 3:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4976.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> *grin*</span><hr size=1> Warrens is hard to prevent runners.  Ideally you want an earth pet or a snarer, or at least be able to cast root/stuns yourself.<br>
<br>
As to where to fight, there's only a few places where I liked to hunt that were safe to sit.... <br>
<br>
1. zone in.. duh... train central though and I avoided it like the plague as soon as I could<br>
<br>
2. by the kitties.  They dont help kobolds.<br>
<br>
3. near the prince, there's a room off to the side<br>
<br>
4. near the king's big hall, the entrance before it, if you sit on the sides, nothing will aggro you there<br>
<br>
Warrens really isnt' a good zone to be solo in.  Even strong solo classes will get adds there and get smushed. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.leagueofhonour.com/images/members/kyrialsignature.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sulissaurnvelve>Sulissa UrnVelve</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Almost dangerous<br>
...but not really</span><br>  Posts: 424<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/29/03 5:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4976.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: *grin*</span><hr size=1> To effectively fight in the warrens you need snare/darkness<br>
<br>
if you don't have it don't bother. Root will break at the exact wrong time and you'll die.<br>
<br>
Other than that  each level playes very differently there in what will assist and what will train etc.<br>
<br>
I've soloed here with ranger and necro, I know an SK and druid that have done well for them selves here as well.<br>
<br>
More or less if one get's away just zone. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wilrethfv>Wilreth FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/29/03 6:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4976.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Warrens</span><hr size=1> My experience seems contrary with most people's, but I <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>LOVE</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> the warrens.  I do suggest you get a group there (However, I suggest you get a group <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>anywhere!</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->).  However, If your soloing I'd suggest level 5 minimum.<br>
<br>
I think it's true for most dungeons, but if you just spend enough time there to see how it works, what the mob's idiosyncracies and paths and agro ranges are, you'll learn &quot;how to do the warrens.&quot;  <br>
<br>
Honestly, I think the entrance is one of the most dangerous places for trains (but, of course the zoneline has it's benefits).  A safer place to set up is near the water (turn left when you enter- you'll eventually get to it- hard to miss).  <br>
<br>
I took a poll of all my recent re-rolls, and 10 out of 12 of my last characters recommend the Warrens for players who re-roll.  Plus Paineel - the best newbie zone for re-rolls who want to do bone chip type quests is directly adjacent.<br>
<br>
Those Heretics know how to party! <br>
<br>
Ramble Ramble Ramble...<br>
<br>
Wilreth<br>
